article.headline: Mississippi Valley St. 28, Alcorn St. 25
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. (AP) -- Aries Nelson threw two touchdown passes and rushed for two more scores as Mississippi Valley State withstood a 15-point fourth-quarter rally Saturday to beat Alcorn State 28-25. Nelson, chosen as the Southwestern Athletic Conference's preseason offensive player of the year, shook off season-long struggles to lift the Delta Devils (6-4, 5-3 SWAC) back into the conference title race. The senior passed for 224 yards and led all players with 96 yards rushing. Less than a minute into the game he found Clarence Cotton at midfield. The receiver broke two tackles on his way to a 66-yard touchdown reception. Nelson added a 10-yard run about 10 minutes later to make it 14-0. The Braves (4-4, 3-3) responded in the second quarter with a 22-yard Jonathan Williams field goal and a 36-yard touchdown pass from Chris Walker to Emmanuel Arceneaux to cut the lead to 14-10. But Nelson hit receiver Tyrone Timmons with an 8-yard touchdown near the end of the half to give the Devils a 21-10 halftime lead. Williams connected on a 25-yard field goal in the fourth quarter and Walker hit receiver Charlie Spiller for a 70-yard touchdown to cut Valley's lead to 21-19 with 4:37 left in the game. Nelson put the Braves away with a 35-yard touchdown run with 1:15 left. Nelson completed 14 of 23 passes in the game. Walker was 17 of 35 for 299 yards with two interceptions. Spiller finished with five catches for 144 yards, while Arceneaux caught six passes for 98 yards.
